      "note": "Lit., \"except him who has ...\", etc. According to the classical commentators - including some of the most outstanding Companions of the Prophet - the \"bond with God\" denotes, in this context, the realization of His oneness and uniqueness; for the wider implications of this term, see surah 2, note 19. Consequently, as pointed out by Razi, even great sinners may hope for God's forgiveness - symbolically expressed by the right of \"intercession\" which will be granted to the prophets on Judgment Day (see note 7 on 10:3) - provided that, during their life on earth, they were aware of God's existence and oneness."
